│                                                            │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                │
│                                                            │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------            │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                │
│ The loop-vectorizer crashes in VPInstruction::execute with │
│ the assertion: "scalar value but not only first lane       │
│ defined". This indicates a mismatch between the value      │
│ generated by a VPInstruction (scalar) and the VPlan's      │
│ expectation that it should produce a vector result unless  │
│ marked as generating only the first lane.                  │
│                                                            │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                    │
│ The debug-only=vplan log shows the vectorized body         │
│ constructing an icmp for the loop exit condition and a     │
│ branch that uses that condition: `%3 = icmp eq i64         │
│ %index.next, 1000; br i1 %3, <null>, label %vector.body`.  │
│ The crash occurs when vectorizing the ir-bb<middle.block>, │
│ which typically hosts control-flow that depends on         │
│ per-part/per-lane scalar conditions (like loop exit        │
│ tests). The vectorizer intends some instructions (e.g.,    │
│ compare/selects driving control flow) to be scalar-only    │
│ for the first lane.                                        │
│                                                            │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                    │
│ In VPInstruction::execute, the logic decides whether a     │
│ recipe generates per-lane vectors or a single scalar for   │
│ the first lane via `GeneratesPerFirstLaneOnly =            │
│ canGenerateScalarForFirstLane() &&                         │
│ (vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) || isVectorToScalar() || │
│ isSingleScalar());`. For instructions where only the first │
│ lane is used, `vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this)` must      │
│ return true. However, VPInstruction::onlyFirstLaneUsed     │
│ currently includes ICmp and PtrAdd but omits Select. In    │
│ patterns like building the loop-exit condition and         │
│ selecting control values, Selects are often used in middle │
│ blocks with only-first-lane semantics. Without handling    │
│ Select, the VPlan expects a vector value from a Select,    │
│ but generatePerPart produces a scalar, triggering the      │
│ assertion.                                                 │
│                                                            │
│ Given the log, the middle.block likely contains a Select   │
│ or a sequence involving Select used to synthesize scalar   │
│ control values. Since Select is missing in the             │
│ onlyFirstLaneUsed switch, the recipe isn't marked as       │
│ "first-lane-only", causing the scalar/vector mismatch.     │
│                                                            │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                 │
│ Add Instruction::Select to                                 │
│ VPInstruction::onlyFirstLaneUsed's switch so it defers to  │
│ vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this), aligning the recipe      │
│ classification with actual usage and allowing scalar       │
│ generation for first lane without tripping the assertion.  │
│                                                            │
│ Edit in llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp     │
│ lines 747-754:                                             │
│ - Current:                                                 │
│   case Instruction::ICmp:                                  │
│   case VPInstruction::PtrAdd:                              │
│     // TODO: Cover additional opcodes.                     │
│     return vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this);               │
│                                                            │
│ - Change to:                                               │
│   case Instruction::ICmp:                                  │
│   case Instruction::Select:                                │
│   case VPInstruction::PtrAdd:                              │
│     // TODO: Cover additional opcodes.                     │
│     return vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this);               │
│                                                            │
│ This mirrors the treatment already present in              │
│ onlyFirstPartUsed where Select is recognized, and brings   │
│ consistency in lane-use analysis.                          │
│                                                            │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                             │
│ By recognizing Select in onlyFirstLaneUsed, the vectorizer │
│ will correctly mark certain Select recipes as generating   │
│ scalar values for the first lane only. This aligns the     │
│ generated type with expectations in                        │
│ VPInstruction::execute, preventing the assertion and       │
│ allowing the loop-vectorizer to proceed correctly on the   │
│ provided reproducer.                                       │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------            │
│                                                            │
